title: An alminacke and prodigious premonstration, made for the yeare of grace. 1566. By Mi. Nostrodamus, The God which eche mans visage well doth see, His temple gates to come for to vnbarre: And Pandores boxe vncouered shall bee, A great thicke cloude for to dissolue fro[m] farre
author: Nostradamus, 1503-1566.
